{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.15","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update."}]},{"level":3,"text":"Enum cases as function references","type":"heading","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect","isActive":true},{"text":" to bundle","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"its output into an action:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict concurrency mo